  "text": "The upstream connection pool overflow condition in Envoy is defined and handled across multiple C++ source files:\n\n**Definition of Overflow State:**\n\n1. **source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc** (lines 138, 176-180, 282-287): This is the primary file that defines and tracks the overflow state. The connection pool emits the `upstream_cx_overflow_` counter when canCreate() returns false, indicating connection circuit breaker limits are hit. It also tracks `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` when maximum pending requests or maximum concurrent requests limits are exceeded.\n\n2. **source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.h**: Defines the `ConnPoolImplBase` class which manages connection pools and tracks overflow through resource manager checks.\n\n3. **source/common/upstream/resource_manager_impl.h**: Implements `ResourceManagerImpl` which provides the `canCreate()` checks that determine if resources (connections, pending requests, requests) are available. When these limits are exceeded, overflow occurs.\n\n**Overflow Emission Points:**\n\n1. **Line 138** (conn_pool_base.cc): `host_->cluster().trafficStats()->upstream_cx_overflow_.inc();` - Incremented when connection creation is blocked due to circuit breaker limits.\n\n2. **Lines 176-180** (conn_pool_base.cc): \"max streams overflow\" - Incremented in `attachStreamToClient()` when enforceMaxRequests() check fails and `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` is incremented.\n\n3. **Lines 282-287** (conn_pool_base.cc): \"max pending streams overflow\" - Incremented in `newStreamImpl()` when `pendingRequests().canCreate()` fails.\n\n**Overflow Handling:**\n\n1. **source/common/router/retry_state_impl.cc** (lines 304-312): The retry logic checks for retry resource exhaustion. When `cluster_.resourceManager(priority_).retries().canCreate()` returns false, it increments `upstream_rq_retry_overflow_` counter and returns `RetryStatus::NoOverflow`.\n\n2. **source/common/router/retry_state_impl.cc** (lines 470-471): Prevents retry when `Http::StreamResetReason::Overflow` is detected - no retry is attempted for overflow conditions.\n\n3. **source/common/router/router.cc**: Sets the `StreamInfo::CoreResponseFlag::UpstreamOverflow` flag when retry status is `NoOverflow` or when connection pool returns overflow failure reasons.\n\n4. **source/common/http/conn_pool_base.cc** (line 178): Handles `StreamResetReason::Overflow` in the HTTP-specific connection pool implementation.\n\n5. **envoy/stream_info/stream_info.h**: Defines the `CoreResponseFlag::UpstreamOverflow` flag which is used to mark responses that encountered upstream pool overflow conditions.\n\nThe overflow condition is ultimately determined by resource limits in the `ResourceManagerImpl` class, which prevents connection creation when circuit breaker limits are reached for connections, pending requests, active requests, or retries."
}

